 hughes medical institute hhmi is an american nonprofit medical research organization based in chevy chase maryland it was founded by the american businessman howard hughes in  it is one of the largest private funding organizations for biological and medical research in the united states hhmi spends about  million per hhmi investigator per year which amounts to annual investment in biomedical research of about  million the institute has an endowment of  billion making it the secondwealthiest philanthropic organization in the united states and the secondbest endowed medical research foundation in the world hhmi is the former owner of the hughes aircraft company  an american aerospace firm which was divested to various firms over time contents  history  see also  references and notes  external links historyedit howard hughes businessman investor pilot film director philanthropist and founder of the institute the institute was formed with the goal of basic research including trying to understand in hughess words the genesis of life itself despite its principles in the early days it was generally viewed as a tax haven for hughess huge personal fortune hughes was hhmis sole trustee and transferred his stock of hughes aircraft to the institute in effect turning the large defense contractor into a taxexempt charity for many years the institute grappled with maintaining its nonprofit status the internal revenue service challenged its charitable status which made it tax exempt partly in response to such claims starting in the late s it began funding  investigators researching at eight different institutions however it remained a modest enterprise for several decades the institute was initially in miami florida in  hughess internist dr verne mason who treated hughes after his  plane crash was chairman of the institutes medical advisory committee the institute moved to coconut grove florida in the mids and then to bethesda maryland in  in  the institute moved to its headquarters in chevy chase maryland it was not until after hughess death in  that the institutes profile increased from an annual budget of  million in  to  million by  in this period it focused its mission on genetics immunology and molecular biology since hughes died without a will as the sole trustee of the hhmi the institute was involved in lengthy court proceedings to determine whether it would benefit from hughess fortune in april  a court appointed new trustees for the institutes holdings in january  the trustees announced they would sell hughes aircraft by private sale or public stock offering on june   general motors gm was announced as the winner of a secretive fivemonth sealedbid auction the purchase was completed on december   for an estimated  billion  billion in cash and the rest in  million shares of gm class h stock the proceeds caused the institute to grow dramatically hhmi completed the building of a new research campus in ashburn virginia called janelia research campus in october  it is modeled after atts bell labs and the medical research councils laboratory of molecular biology with a main laboratory building nearly  feet  m long it contains  square feet  m of enclosed space used primarily for research the campus also features apartments for visiting researchers in  hhmi and the publisher elsevier announced they have established an agreement to make author manuscripts of hhmi research articles published in elsevier and cell press journals publicly available six months following final publication the agreement takes effect for articles published after september   in  the trustees of the howard hughes medical institute selected dr robert tjian as the new president of hhmi in  hhmi awarded fifty researchers as part of the hhmi early career scientist competition in  the hhmi trustees selected dr erin oshea a previous vice president and chief scientific officer at the institute the new president of hhmi see alsoedit list of wealthiest foundations howard hughes medical investigators references and notesedit  chevy chase cdp maryland us census bureau retrieved on march    contact howard hughes medical institute retrieved on march    howard hughes medical institute   year in review  dr verne mason miami physician howard hughes aide dies also treated pershing the new york times november    wernick ellen d howard hughes medical institute retrieved    howard hughes medical institute history funding universe retrieved  june    note the original trustees were helen k copley donald s fredrickson md frank william gay james h gilliam jr esq hanna h gray phd william r lummis esq irving s shapiro esq george w thorn md  staff february   the week in science – february  nature people hhmi president doia retrieved   external linksedit official website  minutes news feature howard hughes patron of science v t e howard hughes aviation hughes aircraft company spruce goose h racer hughes airwest trans world airlines films directed hells angels  the outlaw  films produced two arabian knights  the racket  the mating call  the front page  cock of the air  sky devils  scarface  behind the rising sun  the sin of harold diddlebock  the tattooed stranger  vendetta  his kind of woman  the whip hand  two tickets to broadway  macao  the las vegas story  second chance  the french line  son of sinbad  the conqueror  jet pilot  related jean peters wife howard r hughes sr father hughes tool company howard hughes medical institute desert inn melvin dummar melvin and howard  film the aviator  film rules dont apply  film retrieved from httpsenwikipediaorgwindexphptitlehowardhughesmedicalinstituteoldid categories chevy chase marylandmedical research institutes in the united stateshoward hughesbiomedical research foundationsmedical and health organizations based in marylandfoundations based in the united statesorganizations established in  establishments in marylandbiotechnology organizationshidden categories pages using deprecated image syntaxcoordinates not